# Quality Gates

Lint, security, build, and test failures are defects. Fix them on the branch; do not bypass hooks.

Use these gates:
- `make test`: default deterministic suite, excludes `integration`.
- `make integration`: live browser/network tests.
- `make check-commit`: fast local gate before commit.
- `make lint`: full pre-commit run.
- `make build`: build wheel and sdist with `uv`.

Rules:
- Never use `git commit --no-verify` or skip pre-commit hooks.
- Default tests must not depend on Google, Yahoo, time.is, or other live websites.
- Mark external-site/browser-network checks with `@pytest.mark.integration`.
- If Chrome or a driver is unavailable locally, tests may skip with a clear reason; CI should still run package checks and pure tests.
- Before claiming work is complete, run the relevant fresh commands and report actual results.
